The multilateral forum, long considered a talk shop, has taken on a new significance for Britain as it prepares to leave the European Union. PRETORIA - Queen Elizabeth’s opened the Commonwealth Summit  in London, speaking about the healing hand the 53-nation grouping has on world affairs. In what is probably the last such gathering she’ll attend, the Queen has handed the baton to her son Prince Charles to continue the work done by herself and his grandfather since 1949. Dealing with oceanic pollution is high on the agenda of Commonwealth leaders, including President Cyril Ramaphosa. They’re also expected to bring Zimbabwe back into the fold under its new President Emmerson Mnangagwa. The multilateral forum, long considered a talk shop, has taken on a new significance for Britain as it prepares to leave the European Union. The Commonwealth contains Australia, Canada, India and South Africa among Britain’s top trading partners.